The paper discusses adversarial examples in deep learning for radio frequency signals, specifically in spectrum sensing and survey applications. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). The proposed defense mechanisms also incorporate system-level considerations, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
